What it is: The next generation after IPv4. It uses 128-bit addresses, written like:
2001:0db8:85a3:0000:0000:8a2e:0370:7334
Advantages:
âœ… Huge number of addresses â€“ more than weâ€™ll ever need
âœ… Built-in security features
âœ… No need for NAT (in most cases)

| Feature      | IPv4          | IPv6                       |
| ------------ | ------------- | -------------------------- |
